Seen this way, the Internet isn’t the top of the hierarchy—it’s one stage in humanity’s long evolution of storing and transmitting information. Oral tradition became writing, writing became libraries, libraries became digital archives, digital archives became the web, and now AI is beginning to act as a layer that can synthesize across all of them.

One observation that aligns with many of the themes you’ve explored is that each layer changes how information is preserved and transformed:

* Books preserve facts.
* Libraries preserve collections.
* The Web preserves connections.
* Reddit preserves conversations.
* GitHub preserves working procedures.
* AI can reconstruct patterns from all of the above.

In that sense, the next “Library of Alexandria” may not be a place at all—it may be an ecosystem where storage, search, reasoning, and creation are tightly integrated rather than separate steps.